.RH MOD.RECIPES-SOURCE WIELKANOC-4 D "25 Mar 88" 1989
.RZ "PASCHA" "Cheese Pascha"
.IH "16\-20 servings"
.IG "1" "whole egg"
.IG "4" "egg yolks"
.IG "2 2/3 cups" "sugar" "500 g"
.IG "1 cup" "whipping cream" "250 ml"
.IG "1 cup" "currants or raisins" "150 g"
.IG "2 lbs" "white farmers cheese" "1 kg"
.IG "\(12 lb" "unsalted butter" "250 g"
.IG "1 Tbsp" "vanilla extract" "30 ml"
.IG "1 cup" "chopped blanched almonds" "100 g"
.IG "2 Tbsp" "grated orange peel" "30 ml"
.SK 1
Beat whole egg and egg yolks with sugar until thick and creamy.  Add half of
the cream.  Turn into a saucepan.  Heat almost to a boiling point, stirring
constantly; do not boil.  Remove from heat; add raisins or currants and cover.
.SK 2
Combine the rest of the cream, cheese, butter, and vanilla extract in a large
electric blender.  Blend until smooth.
.SK 3
Turn cheese mixture into a bowl.  Fold in the egg mixture and add the almonds
and orange peel.
.SK 4
Refrigerate 4 hours.  Place in a double thickness of cheesecloth.  Hang over
a bowl in a cold place and let drain for 24 hours.  Chill.  Garnish with nuts
and candied fruit.  Serve cold.  Cut into small slices.
.SH RATING
.I Difficulty:
moderate.
.I Time:
An hour and a day.
.I Precision:
Approximate measurement OK.
.WR
Original recipe passed down through the generations and translated from
Polish into English by
Edward Chrzanowski
MFCF, University of Waterloo, Waterloo, Ontario, Canada
